 context, the New Woman is a distinct articulation resulting from the nation’s tryst with neoliberal reform, consolidation of the middle class, and the ascendency of aggressive Hindu Right politics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aMotion picture industryzIndiazMumbaixHistoryy21st century. 0aWomen in motion picturesxHistoryy21st century. 0aWomenzIndiaxSocial conditionsy21st century. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / General.2bisacsh  aliberalization, liberation, Bollywood, India, Indian women, neoliberal, reform, middle class, Hinduism, Hindu right politics, representation, cinema, sexuality, femininity, Yash Raj, media studies, gender studies, Asian studies, popular culture, new woman, body positive, plus size, politics, contemporary.1 aAnwer, Megha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAnwer, Megha, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aArora, Anupama, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aArora, Anupama, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBanerjee, Koel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBiswas, Madhavi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChakrabarti, Baidurya, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChakraborty, Debadatta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDe, Aparajita, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDesai, Jigna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDora-Laskey, Prathim-Maya, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGehlawat, Ajay, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGhosh, Tanushree, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb